I"*<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Meanwhile they drank their beer, nursed their sick, idled, or <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="doped themselves with work - (dope - 麻醉药物)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(忙于工作)</code></b>, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="filed documents"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(整理归档文件)</code></b> in offices, or played the phonograph at home, without betraying any difference from the rest of us.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Everything was <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="taken"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(忍受/容忍)</code></b> as it came.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Or when, quite unexpectedly, by some kindly chance, they felt a <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="一阵[痛] a sudden sharp stab of pain"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">twinge</code></b> of jealousy, none the less acute for its objectlessness.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>So completely were they dominated by the plague that sometimes the one thing they <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="aspired to"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(渴望)</code></b> was the long sleep it brought, and they caught themselves thinking: “A good thing if I get plague and have <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="done with it"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(因为病情长睡不起)</code></b>!”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Now, on the other hand, they took an interest only in what interested everyone else, they had only general ideas, and even their tenderest affections now seemed abstract, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="items of the common stock"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(普通、没有多大意义的东西)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>What with the gunshots echoing at the gates, the punctual thuds of <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="rubber stamps"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(印章)</code></b> making the rhythm of lives and deaths, the files and fires, the panics and formalities, all alike were <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="pledged to - (常用语圣经中)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(被许诺或是注定会)</code></b> an ugly but recorded death, and, amidst <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="\ ˈnäk-shəs \ 有害的；有毒的；败坏道德的"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">noxious</code></b> fumes and the muted clang of ambulances, all of us <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="ate the same sour bread of exile"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(共饮流放这一杯苦酒)</code></b>, unconsciously waiting for the same reunion, the same miracle of peace regained.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>No doubt our love persisted, but in practice it served nothing; it was <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="an inert mass within us"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(我们体内没有活力的物质)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>And, finally, it is worth noting that those who were parted ceased to enjoy the curious privilege that had been theirs <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="at the outset"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(开始/起初)</code></b>. They had lost love’s egoism and the benefit they derived from it.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>In other words, they had ceased to choose for themselves; plague had <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="leveled out"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(把...弄平/持平/达到平衡)</code></b> discrimination. This could be seen by the way nobody <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="troubled about"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(为...操心)</code></b> the quality of the clothes or food he bought.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The town was peopled with sleepwalkers, whose <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title=""><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">trance </code></b>was broken only on the rare occasions when at night their wounds, to all appearance closed, suddenly reopened.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>However, this account of our predicament <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="gives only the broad lines"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(只给出了大致的轮廓)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
